1985 — Zilog Z800, 1987 — Zilog Z280

Mostly compatible extension of the Zilog Z80, released first as the Z800, later as the Z280. It was first intended as a coprocessor to the incompatible Zilog Z8000, and could use its never released floating coprocessor, the Zilog Z8070.

Physical address space
24-bit
Virtual address space
16-bit
I/O space
